Consider [XSLT](https://stackoverflow.com/tags/xslt/info) with Python&#39;s third-party module, `lxml` (which you possibly already have with `BeautifulSoup` integration). Specifically, call the [identity transform](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Identity_transform) to copy XML as is and then run the `normalize-space()` template on all text nodes.

**XSLT** *(save as .xsl, a special .xml file or embedded string)*

    &lt;xsl:stylesheet version=&quot;1.0&quot; xmlns:xsl=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform&quot;&gt;
        &lt;xsl:output indent=&quot;yes&quot;/&gt;
        &lt;xsl:strip-space elements=&quot;*&quot;/&gt;
        
        &lt;!-- IDENTITY TRANSFORM --&gt;
        &lt;xsl:template match=&quot;@*|node()&quot;&gt;
          &lt;xsl:copy&gt;
            &lt;xsl:apply-templates select=&quot;@*|node()&quot;/&gt;
          &lt;/xsl:copy&gt;
